# Local Claude Code tooling config. Netlify serves the repo root, so files
# committed here would be published to the live site — EXCEPT that _redirects
# now blocks the /.claude/* path from being served to visitors.
#
# Ignore everything under .claude/ (local caches, session state) but allow
# settings.json, which holds the shared "ask before committing" guardrail.
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
